*5.3.x*    (SVN snapshot)

    snmplib:
      - [BUG 1397891]: Re-fix unsigned comparisons against 0
      - [BUG 1397906]: Fix signedness of return values.
      - [BUG 1399370]: Remove broken assertion
      - [BUG 1399370]: Report a failure to build the PDU.
      - [BUG 1445089]: Use the defined default port (if specified) for
           numeric IPv6 addresses, rather than hardwiring SNMP_PORT.
      - [BUG 1459665]: Handle malformed Display Hints sensibly,
           rather than going into an infinite loop.
      - [BUG 1516045]: Handle long (dynamic-buffered) messages correctly.
      - [BUG 1537459,1540745]: Fix missing MIB parsing tokens
      - [BUG 1554989]: Fix handling of OID comparisons.
      - [BUG 1600171]: Support longer community strings in VACM config.
      - [BUG 1660061]: Validate engineIDs more strictly.
      - [PATCH 1510032]: Accept -Z 0 values for engineBoot/engineTime.
      - [PATCH 1548670]: Fix range checks for unsigned integers
      - [PATCH 1553447]: responses will get sent from the original
           dest IP address when possible.
      - [PATCH 1562168]: check for a sock fd less than 0.
      - [PATCH 1565293]: UDPIPv6 transport reports wrong port number
      - [PATCH 1570650]: create a logging shutdown function to properly
           clean up log registrations if needed.
      - [PATCH 1592706]: Fix memory leak when cloning varbinds.
      - [PATCH 1634620]: Fix leaks from create_user_from_session failure.
      - [PATCH 1640114]: Don't store trailing null character.
      - [PATCH 1641895]: Extend short view masks (as per RFC specs)
      - [PATCH 1641972]: add missing const


